WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:01.900
<i>Amy: Previously on "heartland":</i>

00:01.936 --> 00:03.268
- Look at that one!
- Yeah.

00:03.270 --> 00:04.770
- His markings are so cool.

00:04.772 --> 00:06.371
- I'm gonna gentle him
for my dad's wife.

00:06.440 --> 00:08.406
- Peter!
(car door slams)

00:08.442 --> 00:09.808
- What are you doing here?

00:09.943 --> 00:12.244
- I think we should
probably talk, right?

00:12.313 --> 00:14.045
- Yes. To what?

00:15.249 --> 00:17.182
- To the party that you
were talking about.

00:17.218 --> 00:20.385
To... To celebrating our
marriage with the family.

00:22.189 --> 00:25.924
Small and simple, right?
- (scoffs) yeah.

00:26.060 --> 00:27.659
- Well, did you mean
what you said?

00:27.661 --> 00:30.161
- (sighs) yes, I meant it.

00:32.233 --> 00:34.466
Does that scare you?
- No, I'm here, aren't I?

00:34.601 --> 00:37.535
♪♪♪

00:40.741 --> 00:43.609
Amy: Hup! Hup!
Come on! Get up!

00:43.611 --> 00:45.344
Hup! Hup! Hup!

00:45.479 --> 00:48.012
Good boy. Get up. Hup!

00:48.049 --> 00:50.549
(the paint grunts)
- hey, easy.

00:50.618 --> 00:52.117
Easy.

00:54.288 --> 00:55.821
Hey, what's this?

00:57.624 --> 00:59.825
It's not gonna hurt you, okay?
(the paint grunts gently)

00:59.827 --> 01:01.693
It's all right. I know.

01:02.930 --> 01:05.029
I'm gonna put this
on your back, all right?

01:06.067 --> 01:07.499
It's okay.

01:07.568 --> 01:09.701
Good boy.

01:09.703 --> 01:12.770
(the paint nickers)
good. There you go.

01:12.807 --> 01:14.973
Okay. Come on.

01:14.975 --> 01:17.142
(approaching hooves thud)

01:18.446 --> 01:20.378
Tim: Hey, amy.
(the paint whinnies)

01:20.448 --> 01:22.046
- Whoa. Whoa.
You're okay.

01:22.083 --> 01:24.115
What're you doin' here, dad?
(the paint neighs)

01:24.151 --> 01:25.784
- Well, hi to you, too.

01:25.919 --> 01:28.787
- I just mean I thought you had
to prepare for this weekend.

01:28.789 --> 01:31.390
Aren't you the self-appointed
party planner?

01:31.525 --> 01:33.925
- I, I am planning,
as we speak.

01:33.961 --> 01:36.461
That's why I came to see what
the progress was on this horse,

01:36.530 --> 01:37.829
This wildie.

01:39.299 --> 01:41.133
- (sighs)

01:41.202 --> 01:43.935
(door slams,
footsteps crunch on gravel)

01:44.004 --> 01:49.208
♪♪♪

01:49.343 --> 01:51.343
(knocking)
- peter?

01:51.345 --> 01:54.479
(handle rattles,
lou raps on the door)

01:54.482 --> 01:56.014
Peter?

01:56.150 --> 02:01.085
♪♪♪

02:01.122 --> 02:04.823
♪♪♪

02:04.825 --> 02:07.025
- I just still can't believe
that tim

02:07.094 --> 02:09.828
Is committed to this wedding
ceremony thing.

02:09.963 --> 02:12.698
- It's not a wedding
or a ceremony.

02:12.833 --> 02:15.167
He and jessica
just want an evening

02:15.302 --> 02:17.269
With the family to celebrate.

02:17.338 --> 02:19.571
- A small barbecue
at the dude ranch.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.707
That is what tim
has promised me,

02:21.842 --> 02:23.508
And I am holding him to it.

02:23.577 --> 02:25.643
- Well, if there's anything
I can do to help,

02:25.679 --> 02:27.312
You let me know.
- He said he's got it

02:27.348 --> 02:29.781
All taken care of.
It's not gonna be a big thing.

02:29.850 --> 02:32.517
A few steaks, little bit of
wine, little conversation -

02:32.586 --> 02:34.786
Very casual.
(footsteps recede)

02:36.290 --> 02:39.457
- See? Next step is to get him
comfortable with the saddle.

02:39.493 --> 02:41.793
But I think we've come
a long way.

02:41.862 --> 02:43.328
- (sighs) yeah, I was,

02:43.330 --> 02:45.430
I was hoping you'd made
a little more progress.

02:45.432 --> 02:47.065
- Dad, this is a wild horse.

02:47.201 --> 02:48.300
You don't gentle them
overnight.

02:48.435 --> 02:50.135
- Right, I know, I get it.

02:50.137 --> 02:52.204
- To do this properly,
it takes months.

02:52.273 --> 02:54.039
Why are you so impatient?

02:54.174 --> 02:56.708
- I wanted to give him to
jessica as a gift at the party.

02:56.843 --> 02:58.876
- (scoffs)
the party this weekend.

02:58.878 --> 03:00.913
- Ah, it's a big ask, I know.

03:01.048 --> 03:03.548
- (sighs) dad, I just don't
think I can do that.

03:03.617 --> 03:06.084
- I just, I just wanted it
to be a surprise and--

03:06.153 --> 03:08.920
Oh! And this.

03:09.056 --> 03:10.555
(jacket rustles)

03:10.591 --> 03:11.823
(box clicks open)

03:11.959 --> 03:14.026
- Uh... An engagement ring?

03:14.028 --> 03:15.961
- I was walking past
the jewellery store.

03:16.030 --> 03:18.096
I, I don't know
what came over me.

03:18.098 --> 03:19.765
Spoke to me.

03:19.767 --> 03:21.499
(box clicks shut)
back to business.

03:21.535 --> 03:24.436
I have full faith that
if you put your mind to it,

03:24.505 --> 03:27.306
You're gonna have
this wildie ready.

03:27.308 --> 03:29.574
It's gonna mean so much
on the big day.

03:29.643 --> 03:31.543
- So, now this is
the "big day?"

03:31.612 --> 03:34.246
- Yeah! Yeah, good luck.

03:34.315 --> 03:36.114
- (chuckles)

03:38.785 --> 03:45.657
♪♪♪

03:45.792 --> 03:53.932
♪♪♪

03:54.001 --> 03:56.335
♪ and at the break of day ♪

03:56.337 --> 04:01.072
♪ you sank into your dream ♪

04:01.108 --> 04:02.774
♪ you dreamer ♪

04:02.776 --> 04:04.843
♪ oh, oh, oh, oh... ♪

04:04.978 --> 04:06.978
♪ you dreamer ♪

04:09.483 --> 04:13.084
♪ you dreamer ♪

04:19.960 --> 04:21.693
(approaching car rumbles)

04:24.031 --> 04:25.297
- Hey!
- (sighs)

04:25.366 --> 04:26.965
You came back.

04:27.100 --> 04:28.566
- Yeah, I was just doing
a maggie's run.

04:28.636 --> 04:31.369
I mean, I thought that when
you stayed in the dude ranch

04:31.405 --> 04:33.171
It was complete
breakfast service,

04:33.173 --> 04:34.906
But, you know,
maybe I'm mistaken.

04:35.042 --> 04:37.976
- Right. No, no, no, it is.
I'm sorry.

04:38.045 --> 04:40.244
- Oh, oh, I'm just kidding.
Are you okay?

04:40.281 --> 04:42.980
- Yeah, I, I kinda thought
you changed your mind

04:43.017 --> 04:44.982
And made a break for it.
(clears throat)

04:45.019 --> 04:47.185
- What? No! Gosh, no.

04:47.321 --> 04:48.787
You really think I'd do
something like that?

04:48.856 --> 04:50.789
We haven't even had a chance
to talk yet. I mean...

04:50.791 --> 04:52.524
With the kids and family
around all the time,

04:52.659 --> 04:54.326
It's been a little difficult,
you know?

04:54.461 --> 04:56.595
- Yeah, well it's also hard
to concentrate on anything

04:56.730 --> 04:58.663
With you around.
- Oh yeah?

04:58.699 --> 05:00.332
- Mm-hmm.
- (chuckles softly)

05:02.403 --> 05:05.270
But... We really do
need to talk.

05:05.272 --> 05:06.538
- Yes. Yes.
- Right? Okay.

05:06.607 --> 05:08.473
- We do.
- Let's do it.

05:08.509 --> 05:10.876
Lay all our cards on the table
and just uh...

05:10.878 --> 05:12.677
Get it figured out, you know?

05:12.680 --> 05:14.279
- Right. Yes, absolutely.
- Good.

05:16.016 --> 05:19.417
♪♪♪

05:19.486 --> 05:21.519
<i> Peter: So, tim, jessica,</i>

05:21.521 --> 05:23.421
I've decided to stay
for the party this weekend.

05:23.490 --> 05:25.891
- But I thought you had to go
back to vancouver for work?

05:25.893 --> 05:27.826
- I was able to move some
meetings around, sweetheart,

05:27.895 --> 05:29.827
So...
- Well, that's great, peter.

05:29.863 --> 05:31.496
I hope that you didn't move
your schedule around too much

05:31.565 --> 05:33.365
Because it's just gonna be
a small thing.

05:33.500 --> 05:35.434
You wouldn't be missin' much.
- I wouldn't say that.

05:35.436 --> 05:37.168
- No, I... I really wanna
be there.

05:37.204 --> 05:38.703
I mean, it's family, right, so.

05:38.772 --> 05:40.572
- Yeah, I mean, especially
since georgie couldn't get out

05:40.707 --> 05:42.574
Of her jumping competition
to come home,

05:42.643 --> 05:44.609
I think it's great peter
can be there.

05:44.745 --> 05:46.244
Here.
- Sure!

05:46.313 --> 05:48.547
- Oh! Hey, let me give you
a hand uh... With that.

05:48.549 --> 05:50.448
- Sure!
- Thank you, sir!

05:50.517 --> 05:51.716
- Hey, everybody,

05:51.785 --> 05:54.386
I think we should have dessert
in the living room

05:54.521 --> 05:56.487
Around the fire.
And hurry up.

05:58.225 --> 06:00.125
(plates clank)

06:00.194 --> 06:01.793
(indistinct whispering)
- hey, what're you doing?

06:01.862 --> 06:03.995
Are you crazy?
Cut it out!

06:03.997 --> 06:06.598
- Hey!
- What's up with you guys?

06:06.600 --> 06:08.333
- Nothin'. Just grabbin' these.

06:08.335 --> 06:10.501
I'm gonna bring them in to...
Dessert.

06:11.605 --> 06:14.205
- What is up with you guys?
- Nothing!

06:14.274 --> 06:16.241
(footsteps recede)

06:16.243 --> 06:18.042
Lyndy: (giggles)
- oh, goodness!

06:19.780 --> 06:21.413
- I, uh, wanted to say...

06:22.749 --> 06:24.515
A few words tonight about my...

06:26.019 --> 06:27.752
My beautiful wife.

06:27.821 --> 06:30.688
I want you all to know,
in case you didn't already,

06:30.724 --> 06:33.558
Just how happy she makes me.

06:34.995 --> 06:36.461
- Okay. Save it for the party,
honey. (laughs)

06:36.597 --> 06:38.129
<i> Katie: (laughs)</i>

06:38.165 --> 06:39.631
- There have been lots
of special moments

06:39.700 --> 06:42.434
And celebrations
around this pile of stones,

06:42.436 --> 06:45.770
And tonight,
I just wanted to add one more.

06:45.773 --> 06:47.772
(fire crackles)

06:47.775 --> 06:57.282
♪♪♪

06:57.417 --> 07:00.284
You know you mean
the world to me.

07:01.622 --> 07:04.189
First time I saw you,

07:04.191 --> 07:06.491
I knew I wanted to be with you
the rest of my life.

07:07.995 --> 07:11.296
Jessica cook, will ya marry me?

07:13.534 --> 07:16.935
- Yes, tim, I will marry you.

07:17.070 --> 07:20.071
Again... 'cause I already did.
(laughs)

07:20.140 --> 07:25.510
♪♪♪

07:25.546 --> 07:28.346
(fire crackles)

07:30.317 --> 07:32.517
Wow.
- You like it?

07:33.821 --> 07:36.087
- Uh... Yeah, it's beautiful.

07:37.224 --> 07:41.025
♪♪♪

07:41.094 --> 07:45.129
(clapping)
- (laughs happily) aw!

07:45.131 --> 07:49.834
♪♪♪

07:49.836 --> 07:52.237
(footsteps thud on stairs)

07:52.239 --> 07:55.240
- Well, I hope ya didn't mind
the grand gesture.

07:55.242 --> 07:57.976
You know, I just wanted people
to be a part of the proposal,

07:58.045 --> 08:00.177
Since they missed it
in the first place.

08:00.214 --> 08:01.612
- I get it.

08:02.916 --> 08:05.717
I ju-- I just don't know why

08:05.719 --> 08:07.652
A ring was necessary.

08:07.721 --> 08:10.055
I mean, now I have this
crazy diamond on my finger

08:10.190 --> 08:13.258
And... I never asked for that.

08:13.260 --> 08:15.060
- What's wrong with letting
people know we're married?

08:16.463 --> 08:18.263
I'm proud to be married.

08:18.332 --> 08:19.798
- Well, I am too,

08:19.800 --> 08:21.332
I just didn't think
that we were doing rings.

08:21.368 --> 08:22.734
I mean, we did our bracelets
and...

08:22.869 --> 08:24.402
- Well, now you have both.

08:25.906 --> 08:28.806
- 'kay, so I told you,
I don't want a big fuss,

08:28.876 --> 08:30.341
And you promised that
this weekend

08:30.377 --> 08:32.177
Was just gonna be a small,
family affair.

08:32.179 --> 08:33.845
- It will.
- 'kay.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.280
- It will.

08:38.151 --> 08:40.285
I promise!

08:40.287 --> 08:41.986
No more grand gestures.

08:44.024 --> 08:46.891
Mm-kay?
- It is really nice.

08:46.927 --> 08:49.360
(chuckles)
- I know, right?! (laughs)

08:51.532 --> 08:53.031
(birds chirp)

08:53.100 --> 08:54.966
(leaves rustle in the wind,
horse whinnies in the distance)

08:56.737 --> 08:59.237
(bag rustles)

08:59.306 --> 09:01.639
(zipper rasps)

09:01.675 --> 09:03.374
(items rustle)

09:04.645 --> 09:06.377
(box clicks open)

09:06.413 --> 09:10.514
♪♪♪

09:10.551 --> 09:12.317
(box thuds on table)

09:12.319 --> 09:21.258
♪♪♪

09:21.295 --> 09:22.960
(sharp exhale)

09:25.465 --> 09:27.398
(footsteps approach)

09:27.434 --> 09:29.467
Jack: Jessica says
the water pressure

09:29.603 --> 09:31.869
In the shower isn't great.

09:31.939 --> 09:34.139
I came to see what I could do.
- I fixed it already.

09:34.274 --> 09:35.740
Fine, she's gonna love it.

09:35.776 --> 09:37.742
Just, you wasted your trip.
Thanks!

09:39.546 --> 09:42.380
- Ah, what's wrong with you?
What are you hidin'?

09:49.356 --> 09:50.955
- I tried it on.

09:52.559 --> 09:54.959
And all kinds of memories
of my wedding to marion

09:55.028 --> 09:56.961
Came flooding back.

09:58.031 --> 09:59.664
I still remember her

10:00.767 --> 10:02.667
Coming down the aisle...

10:03.770 --> 10:05.536
With you.

10:07.441 --> 10:09.974
She was so beautiful,

10:09.977 --> 10:12.109
And your face looked like
a thundercloud.

10:13.513 --> 10:16.848
I alternately feared you
and loathed you back then.

10:16.983 --> 10:19.184
- Well, the feeling was mutual.

10:21.221 --> 10:23.588
- Well, we've come a long way.

10:23.590 --> 10:26.424
- (sucks his teeth)
for better or for worse.

10:26.493 --> 10:28.526
- Mostly for better.
- (laughs)

10:28.528 --> 10:29.960
- Jack.

10:32.165 --> 10:34.331
You're basically
my best friend.

10:38.472 --> 10:41.205
So, I was wondering
if you would...

10:42.275 --> 10:45.944
Stand up for me;

10:46.079 --> 10:47.746
Be my best man.

10:47.748 --> 10:51.549
- Wasn't this supposed to be
a little family party?

10:51.551 --> 10:52.884
- It is, exactly.

10:53.019 --> 10:54.785
It's, it's...
Exactly what it is.

10:57.891 --> 11:00.425
I, I was hoping you'd
stand up with me.

11:00.427 --> 11:04.763
♪♪♪

11:04.898 --> 11:06.497
- (chuckles softly)

11:10.537 --> 11:12.537
I'd be honoured.

11:12.539 --> 11:19.477
♪♪♪

11:25.652 --> 11:27.185
Amy: That's it, logan.

11:27.254 --> 11:29.186
Yeah, just get him used to
how it feels on his back.

11:29.222 --> 11:30.588
- All right.

11:30.657 --> 11:32.390
- Here we go,
he's doing pretty good.

11:32.392 --> 11:34.658
He doesn't seem phased with
that. We'll try the saddle.

11:34.695 --> 11:36.060
- Okay.
- Are you ready?

11:36.129 --> 11:37.695
- Yeah.

11:37.698 --> 11:38.897
(leather creaks)

11:39.032 --> 11:40.765
(the paint grunts gently)
- whoa.

11:40.900 --> 11:42.767
- Ho... Good boy. It's okay.

11:42.903 --> 11:45.336
Look at you! Good boy!
- Hey.

11:45.372 --> 11:47.338
- (chuckles)
- good boy.

11:47.374 --> 11:49.340
- All right, that's all
we'll do for right now.

11:49.409 --> 11:51.342
You're a good boy.

11:51.344 --> 11:53.244
(approaching hooves thud)
parker: Hey, logan!

11:54.581 --> 11:56.013
<i> Wow, you almost got him</i>
<i> saddled.</i>

11:56.083 --> 11:58.115
You're amazing.
Amy: (chuckles)

11:58.151 --> 11:59.851
- Is it true that tim's
giving him to jessica

11:59.986 --> 12:01.486
As a wedding gift?

12:01.555 --> 12:03.487
- Well, it's not a wedding,
but--

12:03.489 --> 12:05.590
- Come on, katie told me
tim proposed last night

12:05.592 --> 12:07.091
<i> And there was a ring</i>
<i> and everything.</i>

12:08.628 --> 12:10.929
It's so romantic.
- (chuckles)

12:12.132 --> 12:14.332
- So, are you going
to the wedding?

12:14.467 --> 12:16.367
- Oh, I'm not really big
into wedding crashing, so.

12:16.369 --> 12:18.770
- Guys, this is not a wedding.

12:18.905 --> 12:20.705
And yes, logan, you're coming.

12:20.707 --> 12:22.507
You have helped me
with this horse.

12:22.509 --> 12:24.375
We're giving him to jessica
and I want you to be there.

12:24.444 --> 12:26.110
- I don't wanna butt in.

12:26.146 --> 12:28.045
I mean, isn't it just
gonna be family?

12:28.081 --> 12:30.882
- Well, I'm going
and I'm not family.

12:31.017 --> 12:33.584
- All right, if you're going,
I'll go.

12:35.956 --> 12:37.588
<i> Parker: Okay!</i>

12:37.624 --> 12:41.158
♪♪♪

12:42.629 --> 12:43.862
(tools clank)

12:45.732 --> 12:46.798
- Hey.

12:49.136 --> 12:50.735
I got this...

12:50.737 --> 12:53.404
This thing running around
my head, a melody.

12:53.440 --> 12:54.773
Does that ever happen to you?

12:54.908 --> 12:56.608
- Oh yeah, I've had that.

12:56.610 --> 12:58.543
- Yeah, except this is a melody
I made up...

12:58.612 --> 13:00.245
Like, myself.

13:00.380 --> 13:02.880
(front-end scoop hums)

13:02.949 --> 13:04.816
So... And I thought,
I wondered...

13:06.286 --> 13:08.485
If jack could take it
and write a song

13:08.522 --> 13:10.688
For jessica and me.
- A song?

13:10.757 --> 13:13.424
- Well, you could play it
at the party.

13:13.460 --> 13:16.493
Like, like you did with amy
for ashley and caleb's wedding.

13:16.530 --> 13:18.162
Remember that?
- Yeah.

13:18.231 --> 13:19.864
(scoop clunks)

13:19.900 --> 13:23.200
If you've forgotten, that
marriage ended in divorce.

13:25.238 --> 13:27.404
- Well, I'm just sayin',
this could be great.

13:29.242 --> 13:32.142
You know,
if-if you can do it.

13:32.179 --> 13:33.778
I'm, I could help.

13:33.780 --> 13:35.513
Like I said, I've got a melody,
but I have words.

13:35.582 --> 13:37.181
- Oh.

13:37.184 --> 13:39.417
- So, you'd just expand on,
on those.

13:39.486 --> 13:42.152
It sounds like...
What I have sounds like this.

13:44.391 --> 13:47.324
(out of tune)
♪ in the long days of summer ♪

13:48.528 --> 13:51.128
♪ we still have each other ♪

13:52.999 --> 13:54.965
(humming)
you know, it's almost there.

13:55.001 --> 13:57.001
- Yeah. Have you shared
this idea with jessica?

13:57.037 --> 13:58.736
- No. She's gonna love it.

13:58.805 --> 14:00.104
- Yeah, okay. Listen,

14:00.240 --> 14:01.805
I'm gonna tell you,

14:03.176 --> 14:04.876
As your best man,

14:06.046 --> 14:09.580
I feel I need to share
something with you.

14:10.750 --> 14:12.717
It's not always time for tim.

14:12.852 --> 14:15.353
This party is not
all about you,

14:15.422 --> 14:16.888
And neither is marriage.

14:16.957 --> 14:20.158
Marriage is a compromise;
it's meeting your wife halfway.

14:20.293 --> 14:23.561
I think you need to have
a refresher course on that.

14:24.698 --> 14:26.363
- A song?
Jack: Yeah.

14:27.634 --> 14:29.300
- It's bad enough that dad
wants me to train this horse

14:29.302 --> 14:31.568
For jessica
on his crazy schedule,

14:31.605 --> 14:33.771
And now he wants us
to sing a song.

14:33.773 --> 14:36.641
- No, first he wants me
to write the song,

14:36.710 --> 14:38.709
And then, he wants us
to sing it.

14:38.778 --> 14:40.111
- Well... I mean,

14:40.180 --> 14:42.179
What, does he want us to put on
a little dance routine, too?

14:42.215 --> 14:43.915
- How do you think I feel?

14:43.984 --> 14:45.849
I'm trying to run
a cattle business

14:45.886 --> 14:48.852
With a guy who has
the attention span of a gnat!

14:48.889 --> 14:50.054
- (chuckles)

14:50.189 --> 14:53.892
♪♪♪

14:54.027 --> 14:56.661
(running footsteps approach,
tim chuckles)

14:56.796 --> 14:58.595
- Hey.
- Oh, look who it is.

14:58.632 --> 15:00.798
- Right here.

15:00.800 --> 15:02.667
- Lyndy and I
have a proposition.

15:02.802 --> 15:05.736
- You do, do ya?
What's that?

15:05.805 --> 15:09.073
- Well, we heard that gg's
gonna be a best man,

15:09.209 --> 15:12.143
And there's a ceremony,
now a song, so...

15:14.547 --> 15:16.213
- Best man and a ceremony?

15:16.215 --> 15:17.748
- (guilty exhale)

15:17.784 --> 15:20.918
<i> - So, this is officially</i>
<i> a wedding, right?</i>

15:20.954 --> 15:22.921
Well, I've always wanted
to be a bridesmaid,

15:23.056 --> 15:24.789
And lyndy wants to be...

15:24.924 --> 15:27.225
- A flower girl.
- Ooh!

15:27.360 --> 15:30.094
- So, would it be okay?
Would you guys mind?

15:30.096 --> 15:33.263
- I... I think it'd be great.
Right, jess?

15:35.035 --> 15:37.234
- Yes, of course.

15:37.236 --> 15:38.803
<i> Lisa: That's very sweet.</i>

15:38.938 --> 15:40.371
Girls, we'll have to pick out
some very nice dresses.

15:40.506 --> 15:42.173
What's your colour scheme,
jess?

15:42.308 --> 15:44.575
- Uh, I don't know.
Ask tim.

15:44.611 --> 15:50.081
♪♪♪

15:53.486 --> 15:55.219
(door opens,
water runs from faucet)

15:55.221 --> 15:56.921
(footsteps approach)

15:56.923 --> 15:59.057
- Hey, where were you?
You missed dinner.

15:59.192 --> 16:01.325
- Yeah, I know, um,
but I had to work late

16:01.328 --> 16:03.061
And then peter came by,

16:03.063 --> 16:05.329
So we went and checked out
this cute, new bistro.

16:05.365 --> 16:07.031
It's so good.

16:07.167 --> 16:08.800
- I hope you know
what you're doing.

16:08.802 --> 16:10.134
- About what?

16:12.806 --> 16:14.238
Okay. Okay, fine.

16:15.976 --> 16:19.277
The last few days with peter
have literally been perfect.

16:19.412 --> 16:22.213
Like, I'm, I'm giddy.
It's, it's crazy.

16:22.215 --> 16:24.248
It's like we're high school
sweethearts or something.

16:24.284 --> 16:27.284
- And I am happy you're happy,
I am, but...

16:29.155 --> 16:31.355
- But what?
- (sighs)

16:31.358 --> 16:33.557
Just be careful.

16:33.626 --> 16:35.293
- (deflated exhale)
(footsteps recede)

16:35.295 --> 16:37.228
(crickets chirp outside)

16:39.099 --> 16:41.298
(approaching footsteps thud)

16:41.368 --> 16:43.034
(curtains whoosh)

16:44.571 --> 16:46.504
- I'm goin' to bed.
You comin'?

16:50.977 --> 16:52.310
You okay?

16:53.780 --> 16:55.379
- No, I'm not.

16:57.884 --> 17:00.351
This whole thing has
gotten out of control.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.053
First, it was diamond rings,

17:02.122 --> 17:04.055
And then it's best men,
and now bridesmaids?

17:06.893 --> 17:08.893
- The girls just wanna
dress up, that's all.

17:08.895 --> 17:11.996
- Well, of course!
And I'm not gonna say no!

17:11.998 --> 17:15.533
But now this is officially a
wedding, tim, and I told you,

17:15.535 --> 17:18.069
I told you that that was
exactly what I didn't want.

17:18.204 --> 17:19.937
- Well, what's the big deal?

17:21.707 --> 17:23.474
- (scoffs)

17:27.013 --> 17:28.813
Do you know how many
fancy weddings

17:28.882 --> 17:30.882
I have been to in new york?

17:31.017 --> 17:33.750
And almost all of them
have ended up in divorce.

17:34.888 --> 17:37.354
I don't want us
to be like that.

17:37.390 --> 17:40.691
Our wedding in machu picchu
was perfect.

17:40.826 --> 17:42.393
But this?

17:42.395 --> 17:45.162
This, I mean,
do you have any idea

17:45.231 --> 17:48.031
How much pressure your crazy
plans are putting on me?

17:49.903 --> 17:52.402
- I got carried away.
I'll pull back.

17:55.108 --> 17:58.509
- No, no. We're not just
gonna pull back.

17:58.644 --> 18:01.211
We are calling off this party,
or this wedding,

18:01.247 --> 18:03.981
Or whatever it is,
completely.

18:03.983 --> 18:05.749
(curtains whoosh)

18:06.886 --> 18:09.420
I hate these curtains.
I hate them.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.328
- Thank you very much.

18:17.463 --> 18:19.796
Great room service,
by the way.

18:19.833 --> 18:21.999
- Well, as dude ranch manager,

18:22.001 --> 18:23.868
I would like to personally
apologize

18:24.003 --> 18:25.603
For my previous oversight.
- Oh really?

18:25.605 --> 18:27.804
- Mm-hmm.
- Hmm, well, apology accepted.

18:27.841 --> 18:29.940
I guess.
- Oh.

18:30.009 --> 18:32.943
- This is so great you were
able to sneak away like this.

18:33.012 --> 18:34.945
- Yeah, it is.

18:34.981 --> 18:36.513
- You know, we do need
to be careful,

18:36.549 --> 18:38.248
At least until
we tell the girls.

18:39.419 --> 18:40.418
- Tell the girls?

18:42.222 --> 18:44.155
- Yeah, about this,
about everything -

18:44.224 --> 18:46.891
Us getting back together.
They're gonna need to know.

18:46.893 --> 18:48.626
- Yeah, but don't you think
it's just a little bit

18:48.628 --> 18:50.561
Too soon, though?
I mean,

18:50.563 --> 18:52.897
I love this,
this little bubble -

18:52.966 --> 18:55.499
You, me, this cabin.

18:55.568 --> 18:58.769
Maybe we should just keep this
to ourselves a bit longer.

18:58.771 --> 19:00.238
- Hmm, okay.

19:00.240 --> 19:03.107
I feel like I'm kinda
in a time warp a little bit.

19:03.109 --> 19:05.042
You remember when we first met
and you hid me

19:05.044 --> 19:07.912
From your entire family,
in this very cabin?

19:07.981 --> 19:09.413
You saying you wanna do that
again?

19:09.549 --> 19:11.982
- No, I'm not saying that.
I'm saying...

19:12.051 --> 19:15.253
That I just want this to be
ours for a little bit longer.

19:15.255 --> 19:16.954
Is that so bad?
- Yeah.

19:17.023 --> 19:18.823
- Besides, we can't tell
the girls now,

19:18.825 --> 19:20.791
Right before the party,
wedding thing,

19:20.827 --> 19:22.593
You know, whatever it is.

19:22.728 --> 19:24.729
That would take away from
tim and jessica's celebration.

19:24.864 --> 19:27.531
- That sounds a little
like an excuse, to me.

19:29.202 --> 19:30.935
- Okay, because it is.

19:31.070 --> 19:32.803
Because I wanna keep you
to myself...

19:35.341 --> 19:37.107
For as long as I can.

19:37.143 --> 19:39.343
- (chuckles)

19:39.379 --> 19:42.413
No, okay, fine, we'll wait.
- Okay.

19:43.516 --> 19:45.349
- But this conversation's
not over.

19:45.385 --> 19:47.818
- No, but it is for now.

19:48.888 --> 19:50.354
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

19:50.356 --> 19:53.390
♪♪♪

19:53.426 --> 19:55.493
<i> Jack: Jessica, you here?</i>

19:55.628 --> 19:57.628
- Yeah, yeah, come on up, jack!

19:57.763 --> 20:00.831
- How's the water pressure
in that shower?

20:00.900 --> 20:02.499
- Oh, it's good.
Yeah, it's fine.

20:02.569 --> 20:03.934
- Just checking.

20:06.939 --> 20:08.572
Hey, you got a minute?

20:08.608 --> 20:11.642
We haven't had a chance
to talk much,

20:11.644 --> 20:14.478
One-on-one, you and me.
- Yeah, of course.

20:14.514 --> 20:16.180
Can I get ya a cup of coffee
or...?

20:16.315 --> 20:18.316
- Nah, I'm good.

20:18.318 --> 20:20.050
- Have a seat.

20:21.854 --> 20:25.122
- So, how's everything goin'?

20:25.124 --> 20:26.457
- It's fine. It's fine.

20:27.793 --> 20:30.928
- 'cause I admit I have sensed

20:30.930 --> 20:34.064
A bit of growing reluctance
on your part

20:34.100 --> 20:36.433
About this upcoming
celebration.

20:38.204 --> 20:40.203
- Well, I never figured tim
for a bridezilla,

20:40.240 --> 20:41.905
But here we are.
- (chuckles)

20:45.144 --> 20:46.744
- I'm a little overwhelmed,
jack.

20:46.813 --> 20:48.813
- Yeah, I know.

20:48.948 --> 20:51.349
But I gotta say,

20:51.351 --> 20:54.084
I've never seen tim so happy,

20:54.153 --> 20:55.619
And that's because of you.

20:55.688 --> 20:57.554
He just wants everyone else
to know, too.

20:58.824 --> 21:02.659
<i> Yes, he has his failings</i>
<i> and his weaknesses, but...</i>

21:04.264 --> 21:06.630
You know, when it matters,
he's all in,

21:06.699 --> 21:09.800
And this matters to him
a great deal.

21:11.671 --> 21:14.038
<i> See, tim didn't come</i>
<i> from a big family.</i>

21:14.107 --> 21:15.939
<i> He married into this one,</i>

21:16.009 --> 21:17.708
And despite a tonne of...

21:20.380 --> 21:22.313
Things,

21:22.448 --> 21:25.115
He's become a very important
part of it.

21:28.587 --> 21:30.588
- I'm an only child so I don't
have a lot of family either.

21:32.325 --> 21:35.459
My parents split when
I was pretty young so,

21:35.461 --> 21:38.195
I saw first-hand how a marriage
can go south and...

21:40.166 --> 21:43.534
This is all just a little
new to me and...

21:43.603 --> 21:45.369
Scary.
(nervous chuckle)

21:45.405 --> 21:48.272
- Well, the good news is,
you're not alone.

21:48.274 --> 21:50.607
You got the entire clan
in your corner now.

21:50.677 --> 21:53.077
- (chuckles)

21:53.079 --> 21:54.478
- And tim.

21:54.514 --> 21:56.480
Always.

21:56.482 --> 21:59.750
♪♪♪

21:59.752 --> 22:01.752
- Thank you, jack.
(sniffles)

22:01.887 --> 22:03.421
Both: (chuckle)

22:03.423 --> 22:05.489
- Sure.
- I appreciate it.

22:05.558 --> 22:07.892
(footsteps recede)

22:09.028 --> 22:10.694
- (shaky exhale)

22:12.665 --> 22:14.965
(leather scrapes)

22:17.036 --> 22:18.602
(the paint grunts gently)

22:18.738 --> 22:20.571
(birds chirp)

22:20.706 --> 22:22.106
(leather creaks)

22:22.241 --> 22:23.907
- (chuckles) you're okay.

22:23.976 --> 22:25.643
You handled that really well.
(chuckles)

22:27.547 --> 22:30.247
(the paint snorts softly)
- good boy.

22:30.316 --> 22:33.250
All right, just like I was
doing, send him around.

22:33.386 --> 22:35.986
Use this to keep him going.
- Come on. Come.

22:36.022 --> 22:37.388
(the paint snorts softly,
logan chuckles)

22:37.523 --> 22:39.389
- There we go.
Okay, step back this way.

22:39.391 --> 22:40.724
- Yep.
- There ya go.

22:40.727 --> 22:43.193
- Go.
Both: (chuckle)

22:43.229 --> 22:44.995
Amy: Should we try
the next step?

22:45.031 --> 22:46.864
- Sure.
- Okay, take the pressure off.

22:46.933 --> 22:49.533
Ho. You gonna be a good boy?

22:49.535 --> 22:51.435
You two ready for this?

22:52.672 --> 22:55.238
(the paint grunts gently)
- ho.

22:55.274 --> 22:57.674
(the paint grunts)
- whoa. Hey.

22:58.711 --> 23:01.578
(leather creaks)
- good boy! See?

23:04.083 --> 23:05.483
(leather creaks)
good boy.

23:07.553 --> 23:09.319
All right, logan.

23:12.024 --> 23:14.291
- Okay.
- Good boy!

23:14.360 --> 23:16.894
<i> That's it.</i>

23:16.963 --> 23:18.929
(hooves thud)

23:19.064 --> 23:21.031
- Wow, look at that!

23:21.067 --> 23:23.167
(hooves thud, tack jingles)

23:23.169 --> 23:26.303
♪♪♪

23:26.305 --> 23:27.438
(finger taps on screen)

23:31.110 --> 23:34.645
♪♪♪

23:34.714 --> 23:39.650
♪♪♪

23:41.854 --> 23:43.287
Lou: See?

23:43.289 --> 23:44.789
This is a much better place
to have

23:44.924 --> 23:47.591
A serious conversation, right?
- Oh, yes. Yeah, it's great.

23:47.660 --> 23:50.994
- No distractions.
- No, it's official.

23:51.063 --> 23:53.197
No, we really do need
to get on the same page.

23:53.199 --> 23:55.732
- Right, so if we were
to get back together,

23:56.869 --> 23:59.135
What would that look like?
- Uh, great?

23:59.172 --> 24:01.104
Pretty great? Really great?

24:01.140 --> 24:02.473
- Peter.
- Amazing?

24:02.542 --> 24:04.274
- We need to focus.
(phone rings)

24:04.310 --> 24:06.276
- No, I know. I know.
- Just a sec.

24:06.345 --> 24:08.178
Uh, rick, I told you
to hold all my calls.

24:09.982 --> 24:12.749
No. No, I absolutely can't see
anyone right now.

24:14.987 --> 24:16.520
- (whispers) excuse me,
I just wanted to tell you,

24:16.656 --> 24:18.422
You look really hot
when you do mayor stuff.

24:18.424 --> 24:19.490
- (whispers) stop it.

24:19.625 --> 24:21.425
No calls 'til I say.

24:21.427 --> 24:23.894
Peter. Oh, stop, stop, stop.

24:23.896 --> 24:25.795
- Do you have a second?

24:26.833 --> 24:28.832
(light knock on the door,
door opens)

24:28.835 --> 24:30.834
- Oh! Uh... I, I knocked.

24:32.104 --> 24:34.271
I'll go!
- No! No, no, no. It's fine.

24:35.875 --> 24:37.774
- Yeah, I'll just go grab
some, uh, coffee.

24:37.810 --> 24:40.211
- Yeah.
(clears throat)

24:42.548 --> 24:44.781
(sighs)
I, uh, I can explain.

24:44.851 --> 24:46.517
I'm, I'm so embarrassed.

24:46.652 --> 24:48.986
- No, it's good.
It's none of my business.

24:49.055 --> 24:50.754
Both: (laugh)

24:52.525 --> 24:54.358
- Okay, so the reason
why I'm here is...

24:56.061 --> 24:57.728
I've been thinking
that I would like you

24:57.797 --> 24:59.996
To be my maid of honour.
- Your maid of honour?

25:00.032 --> 25:01.999
What? I, I thought this
was just gonna be--

25:02.001 --> 25:03.400
- A small thing?

25:03.536 --> 25:05.736
Yeah, no, it's,
it's officially a wedding.

25:05.871 --> 25:07.804
- Wow.

25:07.840 --> 25:11.341
Well, I would be honoured
to be your maid of honour.

25:12.478 --> 25:14.811
- (happy exhale)
thank you.

25:14.881 --> 25:16.813
That means a lot.

25:16.815 --> 25:18.749
And what happens
in the mayor's office

25:18.751 --> 25:22.019
Stays in the mayor's office.
- Thanks, but really, I um...

25:22.088 --> 25:25.756
I just-- I, I don't want anyone
else knowing about this yet,

25:25.825 --> 25:27.624
Especially katie.

25:30.630 --> 25:32.563
- You're a good mom
for putting her first.

25:34.099 --> 25:35.899
Thanks, lou.

25:35.935 --> 25:37.701
(footsteps recede)

25:37.703 --> 25:40.437
♪♪♪

25:40.573 --> 25:42.072
<i> Tim: Jess?</i>

25:42.074 --> 25:43.907
Jessica: Ah!
- Je-- wh...?

25:43.976 --> 25:45.643
- Hey!
- Are you okay?

25:45.645 --> 25:47.578
<i> - Yeah, yeah, yeah, I was</i>
<i> just getting in the shower,</i>

25:47.647 --> 25:49.780
I just, you just startled me.

25:49.782 --> 25:51.315
Um...

25:53.653 --> 25:56.186
I'm so sorry about last night.

25:56.188 --> 25:58.055
- No.

25:58.057 --> 26:00.490
I'm the one that needs
to apologize.

26:00.560 --> 26:03.259
Let me make something clear.

26:03.296 --> 26:05.596
The reason that I've gone
so overboard -

26:07.466 --> 26:09.800
With the exception of lou
and amy's mother, marion,

26:11.971 --> 26:13.737
I have never,

26:13.739 --> 26:16.172
Ever truly wanted to wear
another wedding band.

26:19.845 --> 26:22.613
And now I really wanna wear
a wedding band.

26:24.116 --> 26:26.783
I can't wait to wear
a wedding band.

26:26.819 --> 26:28.886
And I just wanna tell
everybody important to us.

26:29.021 --> 26:31.121
Everybody I love.

26:31.256 --> 26:33.223
I want them to know it,
I want them to see it.

26:33.259 --> 26:37.260
♪♪♪

26:37.330 --> 26:39.095
- I can't wait to marry you
again.

26:40.165 --> 26:41.965
Thank you for telling me that.

26:42.001 --> 26:48.372
♪♪♪

26:50.309 --> 26:52.609
- I can't wait either.
- Ah, no!

26:52.612 --> 26:55.245
You can't see the dress
before the day. It's bad luck!

26:55.247 --> 26:56.647
- The dress?!

26:56.716 --> 26:58.615
- Yeah, I got a dress.
That's what I was doing,

26:58.618 --> 27:00.050
I was trying it on
when you came in.

27:00.052 --> 27:02.585
- You bought a dress?
- I did, and you can't see it.

27:03.856 --> 27:05.588
- (laughs)

27:05.625 --> 27:07.658
- Did you say wedding bands?

27:07.793 --> 27:13.430
♪♪♪

27:15.201 --> 27:16.800
Lou: I mean it.

27:16.836 --> 27:18.736
I think we should just keep
our distance today

27:18.738 --> 27:21.137
And not let on that anything
is going on between us,

27:21.173 --> 27:22.939
At all.

27:22.941 --> 27:25.041
Not yet.
- Yeah, and I agreed to that.

27:25.043 --> 27:26.944
- I don't wanna give anyone
the wrong impression, okay,

27:26.946 --> 27:29.146
And it's a wedding, peter,
you know us.

27:29.215 --> 27:31.081
We'll get carried away.

27:31.150 --> 27:33.149
- I can't believe
you're doing this.

27:34.253 --> 27:36.887
- I don't wanna get
katie's hopes up, okay?

27:36.889 --> 27:39.456
Not when we don't know
what we are yet.

27:39.525 --> 27:41.425
And we have to do
what's best for our kids.

27:41.560 --> 27:43.961
- What's best for our kids
is being together. Wh...

27:45.164 --> 27:48.098
What's going on? I'm not
seeing it. You have to...

27:48.100 --> 27:49.833
(approaching car rumbles)

27:51.637 --> 27:53.303
Okay, sure.
Yeah, I'll, I'll...

27:53.372 --> 27:55.706
Do my best to pretend
I don't know ya.

27:57.843 --> 27:59.642
(door clicks open)

28:04.850 --> 28:10.287
♪♪♪

28:10.422 --> 28:12.188
- Hey, jade.

28:12.224 --> 28:13.991
It's good to see you.
- You, too!

28:16.362 --> 28:17.728
- I'm proud of you.

28:19.131 --> 28:20.663
- Thank you.

28:23.202 --> 28:24.702
- Hey, caleb.
Thanks for coming.

28:26.439 --> 28:28.171
(small chuckle)

28:28.240 --> 28:30.007
- What's the matter?

28:30.009 --> 28:31.742
- He's not here.

28:31.877 --> 28:33.877
- Who's not here?
- My date.

28:33.913 --> 28:36.613
- Your what?
- My date! Logan.

28:36.749 --> 28:38.148
The boy I told you about.

28:38.283 --> 28:39.783
Where is he?

28:42.388 --> 28:43.920
- (nervous exhale)

28:43.956 --> 28:49.092
♪♪♪

28:49.227 --> 28:52.929
♪ when the rain is blowin'
in your face ♪

28:55.434 --> 28:59.569
♪ and the whole world
is on your case ♪

29:01.907 --> 29:04.040
♪ I could offer you
a warm embrace ♪

29:04.110 --> 29:05.642
- Hi, sweetie.

29:08.013 --> 29:11.648
♪ to make you feel my love ♪

29:11.717 --> 29:18.188
♪♪♪

29:18.257 --> 29:21.658
♪ when evening shadows
and the stars appear ♪

29:24.663 --> 29:28.799
♪ and there is no one
to dry your tears ♪

29:30.936 --> 29:34.938
♪ I could hold you
for a million years ♪

29:36.942 --> 29:39.877
♪ to make you feel my love ♪

29:39.879 --> 29:41.945
